						<summary>

						<p>Stone built into the pavement near the Gōpura in Mukkanṭīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara; Rangarāyadēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1560, Sarvajit, Pushya ba. 12.</hi> Irregular.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to record a gift of land to the temple by Dalavāyi Tipā Nāyanayya who is called the agent of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
